Aerial view of the Coral  Gables campus				"Aerial view of Main Campus in 1929 as it stood from 1926 to 1946. The Merrick Building skeleton and the Don Carlos Apartments (now the Student Health Center)",  "Main Campus-Aerial Views- (1927?), (1926), (1929) Archives: Photo File",  "Rediscovered in "the dungeon" by GR Nov.16, 1972." written on verso of photo. Memorandum accompanying this film from Eugene E. Cohen (VP ) to Dr. Stanford dated Sept. 25, 1962 reads "The attached Aerial photo shows the campus when lots were $150 for 100 feet of good frontage. Suggest this be forwarded to the library for the archives." As of 10/26/2007, the original image is on loan to the Bass Museum of Art.
